-- Thailand Stock Movers: Advanced Info, Premier Marketing, PTTEP
-- B y   T o n y   J o r d a n
-- 2012-07-06T09:55:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/thailand-stock-movers-advanced-info-service-premier-marketing.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  fell 0.1 percent to 1,200.08. The gauge
gained 2.4 percent this week, a second straight weekly advance.  Oil producers:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , the nation’s biggest
company, declined 1.2 percent to 334 baht, its largest drop
since June 25.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the
biggest listed explorer, lost 0.6 percent to 177 baht. Crude oil
futures declined as much as 1.7 percent to $85.70 a barrel in
after-hours trading in New York, extending yesterday’s 0.5
percent slide.  Advanced Info Service Pcl (ADVANC)  , the nation’s biggest
mobile-phone company, gained 1.8 percent to a record 197 baht.
Net income in the second quarter may increase 40 percent from a
year earlier to 8.6 billion baht ($271.8 million), Bualuang
Securities Pcl wrote in a note to clients today.  Premier Marketing Pcl (PM)  , a snack-food distributor,
rose 1.7 percent to 5.85 baht, the highest close since May 23.
Premier Canning Industries Ltd., a subsidiary, paid the company
an interim dividend of 20 baht per share, Premier said today in
a regulatory filing.  Premier Technology Pcl (PT)  , a distributor of audio and
video equipment, rose 4.9 percent to 3.44 baht, the biggest gain
in a week. The company’s Datapro Computer Systems Co. unit paid
an interim dividend of 133 baht per share to Premier, it said
today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
